    "symptoms": [
      "Usually asymptomatic: Many individuals with hypercholesterolemia do not experience noticeable symptoms, making it crucial to have regular cholesterol screenings.",
      "Chest pain: Some may develop chest pain or angina as a result of reduced blood flow to the heart due to arteriosclerosis caused by cholesterol buildup.",
      "Fatigue: As the heart struggles to function properly, individuals may experience unexplained fatigue or weakness.",
      "Xanthomas: These are yellowish deposits of cholesterol that can appear on the skin or tendons, indicating high cholesterol levels."
