    "treatments": "Treatment for hypercholesterolemia often begins with lifestyle changes, including adopting a heart-healthy diet that is low in saturated and trans fats, increasing physical activity, and maintaining a healthy weight. If lifestyle modifications are not sufficient, healthcare providers may recommend medications, such as statins, which help lower cholesterol by inhibiting its production in the liver. Additional medications may include bile acid sequestrants, cholesterol absorption inhibitors, and PCSK9 inhibitors. Regular monitoring of cholesterol levels is essential to evaluate the effectiveness of treatment and make necessary adjustments."
